}
  DUMP file [position [length]] [/A]

This command displays the contents of
the chosen file as both hexadecimal
and ATASCII output. When the /A flag
is used, non-printable characters are
converted to printable ones, making
the listing suitable for printing
(see the PRINT command).

If a starting position is given, the
listing begins there. With a length
value, only that number of bytes is
shown.

Press <CONTROL>+<1> to pause or resume
the listing, or press <ESC> to stop
the command.
